author: National Geographic
description:
Discover the compelling story of Cree and Inuit communities fighting to protect their waters — the lifeblood of families for millenia. Produced by Pristine Seas at National Geographic Society, this film offers an intimate look into the heart of the vital Hudson Bay and James Bay ecosystems.

For countless generations, these thriving waters have sustained communities’ way of life. Through stunning, never-before-seen underwater footage captured by the National Geographic expedition team and gorgeous animations, the film brings to life the emotional and inspiring voices of local communities stepping up to save their homelands.
